{"article_id":"FSlZ96nb0bMNK0nZ","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"As my colleague Simon Maloy deftly explained yesterday ,","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"Matt Bevin ' s Tuesday victory in Kentucky ' s gubernatorial race is yet another sign","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"that the Democratic Party is in trouble .","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"Sure , Bevin is better on the campaign trail","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"than he was during his failed attempt","depth":10},{"id":5,"text":"to oust Sen. Mitch McConnell in 2014 .","depth":10},{"id":6,"text":"But","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"as a recent piece about the race in the Atlantic made clear ,","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"he still isn ' t good .","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"And","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"while the voters of Kentucky are undoubtedly conservative ,","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"a look-over of Bevin ' s political history reveals a man on the wrong side of the line","depth":11},{"id":12,"text":"separating \" hyper-conservative \" from \" radical fringe . \"","depth":11},{"id":13,"text":"But he won , anyway .","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"And","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"despite what pre-election polls suggested ,","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"the outcome wasn ' t even close .","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"This raises myriad questions for the Democratic Party , both in Kentucky and the nation as a whole .","depth":5},{"id":18,"text":"Most of those questions will center on the party ' s get-out-the-vote apparatus ,","depth":6},{"id":19,"text":"which increasingly seems to be useless for any election","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"in which Barack Obama isn ' t a candidate .","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"In general , I chalk that up to the decline of organized labor .","depth":4},{"id":22,"text":"But Kentucky was never exactly Michigan .","depth":6},{"id":23,"text":"( In fact , the state is something of an outlier recently","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"when it comes to the nation ' s larger de-unionization trend . )","depth":7},{"id":25,"text":"Regardless of unions ' strength , though , Democrats had hoped","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"that policy successes would inspire their constituents to come out and vote .","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"Specifically , they hoped","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"that Bevin ' s vow","depth":12},{"id":29,"text":"to dismantle the Affordable Care Act in Kentucky","depth":14},{"id":30,"text":"( as","depth":14},{"id":31,"text":"much as he can ,","depth":14},{"id":32,"text":"that is )","depth":14},{"id":33,"text":"would inspire the hundreds of thousands of Kentuckians","depth":13},{"id":34,"text":"who ' ve benefited","depth":13},{"id":35,"text":"to vote for its protection .","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"By almost any metric , after all , Kynect","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"- what they call the ACA in Kentucky -","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"has been an inspirational success .","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"Democrats hoped","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"voters would reward the party","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"for successfully implementing such a major policy .","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"But from today ' s vantage , it ' s painfully obvious that they didn ' t .","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"And that ' s not just a problem in the Bluegrass State","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"- it ' s a problem for all Democrats .","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"Because one of the foundational assumptions behind Kynect , the ACA , and much of the entire Democratic Party agenda is that good policy makes for good politics .","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"In Kentucky , at least , it didn ' t .","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"What does \" good policy = good politics \" mean ?","depth":5},{"id":48,"text":"It basically means","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"that an effective program can survive ,","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"even if it ' s unpopular at the outset .","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"Those","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"who benefit ,","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"the theory goes ,","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"will eventually become a constituency","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"( if they aren ' t already )","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"and will organize","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"to preserve it .","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"Think of Social Security or Medicare :","depth":5},{"id":59,"text":"They weren ' t necessarily super-popular","depth":7},{"id":60,"text":"when they were first implemented ,","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"but","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"once people started relying on them ,","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"they became the so-called third rail of American politics .","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"But","depth":7},{"id":65,"text":"as left-wing critics of the Democratic consensus have long argued ,","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"there ' s a problem","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"with analogizing the ACA and Social Security .","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"One of the programs is universal","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"- everyone puts in ;","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"everyone takes out -","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"and the other isn ' t .","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"And this isn ' t incidental .","depth":7},{"id":73,"text":"It ' s the reason","depth":7},{"id":74,"text":"why so many Tea Party types will rail against \" handouts \"","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"but cherish their Medicare .","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"It ' s because they believe","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"they ' re simply receiving what they ' re owed","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"( they aren ' t )","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"and that the benefits go to them instead of good-for-nothing moochers .","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"There are plenty of people in Kentucky right now","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"who are better off","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"because of the ACA .","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"But many of them are beneficiaries of the law ' s Medicaid expansion","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"( which Bevin has promised to change ,","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"if not revoke )","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"and thus lack political influence .","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"And the rest ?","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"As far as many of them know ,","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"it ' s not the ACA or \" Obamacare \"","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"that they now rely on .","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"It ' s Kynect .","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"And Bevin didn ' t campaign against Kynect .","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"He campaigned against Obamacare .","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"Kentucky Democrats got the policy right , in other words ;","depth":6},{"id":95,"text":"but it never paid political dividends .","depth":6},{"id":96,"text":"In fairness , it ' s too early to say","depth":4},{"id":97,"text":"the debate is over .","depth":4},{"id":98,"text":"If Bevin tries to make good on his promises","depth":5},{"id":99,"text":"and is greeted with a backlash ,","depth":5},{"id":100,"text":"he may trim his sails","depth":5},{"id":101,"text":"or abandon the initiative .","depth":5},{"id":102,"text":"Still , it ' s not like Democrats didn ' t spend much of the campaign","depth":4},{"id":103,"text":"warning about Bevin ' s plans for health care in Kentucky .","depth":4},{"id":104,"text":"They did","depth":5},{"id":105,"text":"- a lot .","depth":5},{"id":106,"text":"It didn ' t make a difference .","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":213,"left":202,"right":212,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":202,"left":153,"right":201,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":153,"left":127,"right":152,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":127,"left":123,"right":126,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":123,"left":109,"right":122,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":109,"left":0,"right":108,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":108,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":122,"left":119,"right":121,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":119,"left":1